lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia, June 2 -- Prime Minister John Curtin, opening Australia's second uA35,000,000 Liberty War Loan at Melbourne Town Hall, said Japan's program of constant expansion "has at last suffered a stalemate." At the same time Navy Minister Norman J.O. Makin revealed in Canberra that one of three enemy midget submarines was destroyed before it got into Sydney Harbor Sunday and a second before it could fire its torpedoes.
abstract: Australian Navy Min Makin on Jap submarine attack failure, Sydney
